(power_logic, time).explanation: Logic power consumption and timing are both outcomes of the same design decisions but do not directly cause each other in processor architecture;

(power_logic, power_clock).explanation: Logic power and clock power are separate components of total power consumption that operate independently without direct causal relationship;

(power_logic, area_net_area).explanation: Logic power consumption and net area are both consequences of design complexity but do not have a direct causal relationship;
